secondary_outcome.description:
All teeth were visually using the International Caries Detection and Assessment System (ICDAS-II). The chosen sites were recorded as:
0 = sound;
= first visible sign of noncavitated lesion seen only when the tooth is dried;
= visible noncavitated lesion seen when wet and dry;
= microcavitation in enamel;
= noncavitated lesion extending into dentine seen as an undermining shadow;
= small cavitated lesion with visible dentine: less than 50% of surface;
= large cavitated lesions with visible dentine in more than 50% of the surface. A single calibrated examiner measured probing depth-PD, clinical attachment level- CAL, plaque (Pl), and gingival indices (GI), bleeding on probing (BOP) at four sites per tooth using a manual periodontal probe (PCPUNC, Hu-Friedy, Chicago, IL, USA).
